  "prompt": "What causes cotton fabric to shrink? Heated water, cool water or both?",
  "response": "Cotton fabric typically shrinks when exposed to heat and moisture, particularly from hot water. When cotton fibers are washed in hot water, the heat can cause the fibers to tighten and contract. However, cold water can also contribute to some degree of shrinkage, especially if the fabric has been previously preshrunk. \n\nIn summary, while hot water is the primary cause of cotton shrinkage, cool water can also have an effect, particularly if the fabric is agitated or subjected to any mechanical action that disrupts the fibers. To minimize shrinkage, it\u2019s advisable to wash cotton fabrics in cold water and to avoid high heat during drying.",
